    <b><h1><center><u>THE PLANT KINGDOM</h1></b></center></u>
      
        
        <p style="background-color:Tomato;">
   Plants are predominantly photosynthetic eukaryotes of kingdom PLANTAE.Historically the plant kingdom encompassed all living things that were not not animals 
   ,and included algae and fungi;however all current definitions of plantae exclude fungi and some algae,as well as the prokaryotes.
</p>
    <b><i><u><h2>Plant Kingdom’ Features</h2></b></i></u>
        <ul>
          <li><h3>They make their own food hence are called autotrops.</h3></li>

          <li><h3>They are multi-cellular eukaryotes.</h3></li> 

          <li><h3>They are non-motile.</h3></li> 

          <li><h3>Plants contains photosynthetic pigments called chlorophyll present in plastids. </h3></li>

          <li><h3>The plant cell contains outer cell wall and large vacuole.</h3></li>

          <li><h3>They have different organelles for anchorage,support,reproduction and photosynthesis.</h3></li>
        </ul>
<img src="https://www.istockphoto.com/photo/young-plant-growing-in-sunlight-gm658291850-120046061.jpg"  width="500" height="600">
        
    <b><i><u><h2>Names of some plants</h2></b></i></u>
